<plot>Norman and Colette lead separate lives unknowingly bound together by an outdated song warbled through the radio. But when Colette serves Norman a drink one night, a child awakens within each of them. Together they plunge into a more vibrant world. "A Boy and A Girl" is a musical romance, enriched by a know-it-all drag queen, an origami rose, and an immense bowl of chocolate pudding. This film summons the romantic inside of us, who gave up on love because it was all too fantastic.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?007838</url></doc>
